    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;The Point-to-Point Protocol (PPP) provides a standard method for transporting multi-protocol datagrams over point-to-point links.The Extensible Authentication Protocol (EAP) is a PPP extension that provides support for additional authentication methods within PPP.  This memo defines an Experimental Protocol for the Internet community.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
